717760f.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 166th Street (West)
717760f.text:
Broadway, west side, north from and including West 166th (foreground), to and including West 168th (extreme right) Streets, showing ColumbiaPresbyterian Medical Center. The prominent building (center) is the Babies Hospital; on its right, Vanderbilt Clinic; and on its left, Presbvterian Hospital (Sloane Hospital). On the extreme left appears the Preabvterian School for Nursing, between Fort Washington Ave., and
Riverside Drive.
1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Writers Project.

717761f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 166th Street (West)
717761f-a.text:
Broadway, between West 166th (left) and 168th Streets, as seen from St. Nicholas Ave. and across that triangular area known as Mitchell Sduare. Prominent structures shown are units of Columbia UniversityPresbyterian Medical Center which occupy that land west of Broadway to Riverside Drive, from West 165th to 168th Streets. The Babies Hospital
occupies the center of this view.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
